cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper discusses a training algorithm for Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization algorithms, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
